<OUTPUT_TEXT>
When answering telephones, I would greet the caller with a friendly and professional tone, identify myself, and ask how I can assist them. If the caller is requesting to speak with a specific staff member, I would politely inform them of the staff member's availability and either transfer the call or take a message if they are unavailable. If the caller is seeking general information or has a question, I would do my best to provide the necessary information or direct them to the appropriate resource.
